Grad_Rate: High school graduation rate (% of residents), 2017-2021
LDPP_2022: Lead poisoning rate (% of children ages 1-5), 2022

Safety: Number of adults who report that they feel safe in their neighborhood 'all of the time' or 'most of the time'.
Grad_Rate: Residents 25 or older with at least a high school degree: including GED and any higher education
UMP: Percent of residents 16 and older in the civilian labor force who are actively seeking employment.
COI: The education domain of the Child Opportunity Index 2.0 scored as Very Low (5), Low (4), Moderate (3), High (2), and Very High (1)
LEP: Percentage of residents 5 years and older who do not speak English 'very well'.
Lead_Count: Children ages 1-5 with blood lead level at or above 5 micrograms per deciliter
LDPP_2022: Percent of children ages 1-5 with blood lead level at or above 5 micrograms per deciliter

Safety: Chicago Department of Public Health, Healthy Chicago Survey
UMP: American Community Survey (Tables B23025, B23001, and C23002)
Lead_Count: Chicago Department of Public Health, Lead Poisoning Prevention Program
LDPP_2022: Chicago Department of Public Health, Lead Poisoning Prevention Program
